<h1>MOMENTUM Developer Report</h1>
<p class="meta">
<strong>Product:</strong> MOMENTUM (UI brand: FEEDBACK &mdash; &ldquo;Where live music lives online&rdquo;)<br>
<strong>Report date:</strong> June 8, 2026<br>
<strong>Repository:</strong> /Users/user/Documents/GitHub/momentum<br>
<strong>Origin:</strong> Scaffolded via getmocha.com
</p>

<h2>Executive Summary</h2>
<p>MOMENTUM is a full-stack social video platform for live music. Users capture, upload, and discover short concert clips; follow artists, venues, and other fans; and engage around shows, songs, and genres. The backend is feature-complete on Cloudflare Workers; the frontend is a React SPA with a polished core loop but several advanced features built but not fully wired into routes.</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Area</th><th>Maturity</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
<tr><td>Backend API</td><td class="done">~95%</td><td>~170 REST endpoints + WebSocket; broad feature surface</td></tr>
<tr><td>Database</td><td class="done">~95%</td><td>54 migrations; 50+ tables</td></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend core UX</td><td class="done">~85%</td><td>Feed, upload, discover, profiles, clip modal all functional</td></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend advanced</td><td class="partial">~60%</td><td>Live viewer, premium, role dashboards exist but are not routed</td></tr>
<tr><td>Testing</td><td class="partial">~40%</td><td>24 Vitest unit tests; no E2E suite</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Overall</strong></td><td class="done"><strong>~80%</strong></td><td>Production-viable for core clip social loop; polish and wiring remain</td></tr>
</table>

<p>Recent development (2026) has focused on <strong>event/show organization</strong>, <strong>notifications</strong>, <strong>social/following</strong>, <strong>user feed</strong>, and <strong>discover UX</strong> &mdash; not greenfield architecture.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Architecture</h2>

<h3>System Overview</h3>
<pre>
Browser (React 19 SPA)
    |
    |  /api/*  and  /realtime (WebSocket)
    v
Cloudflare Worker (Hono)
    |-- D1 SQLite (momentum-db)
    |-- R2 (momentum-videos, momentum-thumbnails)
    |-- Durable Objects (RealtimeDurableObject)
    |-- Cloudflare Stream
    |
    +-- External: Mocha Users, JamBase, YouTube, Stripe,
                 Ticketmaster, Google Maps, ACRCloud/AudD, Resend
</pre>

<h3>Tech Stack</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Layer</th><th>Technology</th></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend</td><td>React 19, React Router 7, Tailwind CSS 3, Vite 7, TypeScript</td></tr>
<tr><td>Backend</td><td>Hono 4, Zod validation, Cloudflare Workers</td></tr>
<tr><td>Database</td><td>Cloudflare D1 (SQLite)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Storage</td><td>Cloudflare R2 (videos + thumbnails), Cloudflare Stream</td></tr>
<tr><td>Realtime</td><td>Durable Objects + WebSocket at /realtime</td></tr>
<tr><td>Auth</td><td>Mocha Users Service + direct Google OAuth + email/password</td></tr>
<tr><td>Payments</td><td>Stripe (subscriptions, Connect payouts, webhooks)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Email</td><td>Resend (password reset)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Testing</td><td>Vitest (24 test files)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Deploy</td><td>Single Worker serves API + built SPA from dist/</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Project Structure</h3>
<pre>
momentum/
  src/react-app/     ~22 pages, ~92 components, 36 hooks, 34 lib modules
  src/worker/        ~83 files; monolithic Hono router + modular *-endpoints.ts
  src/shared/        Shared types/utils (show IDs, genres, JamBase helpers)
  migrations/        54 numbered SQL migrations
  docs/              Cloudflare setup, staging, upload-outbox design
  scripts/dev.mjs    Smart dev launcher (Vite + optional Wrangler)
  wrangler.json      D1, R2, DO bindings
</pre>

<h3>Dev Environment</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Node:</strong> ^20.19.0 or &gt;=22.12.0</li>
<li><strong>npm run dev</strong> &mdash; auto-detects macOS version; proxies /api to Wrangler on older macOS</li>
<li><strong>npm run db:migrate:local</strong> &mdash; required on fresh clone</li>
<li><strong>DevContainer</strong> &mdash; full D1/R2/DO parity on Linux</li>
<li><strong>Optional:</strong> Docker Compose Postgres (supplementary; D1 is primary)</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Feature Catalog</h2>

<h3>1. Authentication &amp; Identity</h3>
<p><strong>Status: Production-ready (hybrid auth)</strong></p>
<p>Three parallel session systems resolved by hybrid-auth.ts:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Mocha Users Service</strong> &mdash; primary Google OAuth path</li>
<li><strong>Direct Google OAuth</strong> &mdash; fallback via google_accounts / google_sessions tables</li>
<li><strong>Email/password</strong> &mdash; email_accounts, email_sessions, password reset via Resend</li>
</ol>

<table>
<tr><th>Feature</th><th>Backend</th><th>Frontend</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
<tr><td>Google OAuth sign-in</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>/auth, /auth/callback</td></tr>
<tr><td>Email signup/signin</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>Full flow with validation</td></tr>
<tr><td>Password reset</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>/auth/reset-password</td></tr>
<tr><td>Session cookies</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>credentials: include via apiFetch</td></tr>
<tr><td>Account linking</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>Merges Google + email identities across ~18 tables</td></tr>
<tr><td>Device tokens (Remember Me)</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>DeviceManagement in profile editor</td></tr>
<tr><td>Two-factor auth (TOTP)</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="partial">Partial</td><td>Backend complete; limited UI exposure</td></tr>
<tr><td>Logout</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td class="done">Yes</td><td>Clears all session types</td></tr>
</table>

<p><strong>User roles</strong> (stored on user_profiles.role): fan (default), artist, venue, influencer, ambassador. Additional flags: is_admin, is_moderator, is_verified, is_premium.</p>

<h3>2. User Profiles &amp; Onboarding</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Feature</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>Onboarding (/onboarding)</td><td>3-step flow: role selection, profile basics, location + favorite artists</td></tr>
<tr><td>Public profiles (/users/:userId)</td><td>Stats, clips grid, follow button, gamification hub</td></tr>
<tr><td>Profile editor</td><td>Display name, bio, images, location, favorite artists, device management</td></tr>
<tr><td>Verification</td><td>Users submit proof; admins approve/reject via admin panel</td></tr>
<tr><td>Privacy settings</td><td>Profile visibility, tagging, notification toggles (GDPR component exists)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Profile analytics</td><td>Profile view tracking</td></tr>
<tr><td>Own profile hub</td><td>Points, badges, my clips, saved clips, shows attended</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>3. Clip Content (Core Product)</h3>
<p>The central content unit is a <strong>clip</strong> &mdash; a short concert video with rich metadata.</p>

<h4>Upload Pipeline</h4>
<table>
<tr><th>Step</th><th>Implementation</th></tr>
<tr><td>Capture</td><td>Quick Record modal (mobile) or /upload page</td></tr>
<tr><td>Video storage</td><td>R2 direct upload + resumable chunked upload</td></tr>
<tr><td>Stream processing</td><td>Cloudflare Stream ingest, status polling, thumbnails</td></tr>
<tr><td>Metadata</td><td>Artist, venue, location, song, genre, show/event, geolocation</td></tr>
<tr><td>Auto-tagging</td><td>JamBase show matching by geolocation + timestamp</td></tr>
<tr><td>Song ID</td><td>ACRCloud (primary) + AudD (fallback) during upload/capture</td></tr>
<tr><td>Background upload</td><td>ClipUploadQueueContext &mdash; up to 5 queued jobs with retry</td></tr>
<tr><td>Drafts</td><td>is_draft flag; publish when ready</td></tr>
</table>

<h4>Clip Engagement</h4>
<table>
<tr><th>Action</th><th>API</th><th>UI</th></tr>
<tr><td>View</td><td>POST /api/clips/:id/view</td><td>Fire-and-forget analytics</td></tr>
<tr><td>Like</td><td>POST /api/clips/:id/like</td><td>Animated heart in modal + feed</td></tr>
<tr><td>Save/bookmark</td><td>POST /api/clips/:id/save</td><td>/saved page</td></tr>
<tr><td>Comment</td><td>Threaded comments API</td><td>CommentSection in clip modal</td></tr>
<tr><td>Rate (1&ndash;5 stars)</td><td>Rating endpoints</td><td>StarRating component</td></tr>
<tr><td>Share</td><td>Share tracking + Web Share API</td><td>Share sheet in modal</td></tr>
<tr><td>Report/flag</td><td>Moderation queue</td><td>Report from clip modal</td></tr>
<tr><td>Favorite by artist</td><td>Per-artist favorite clip</td><td>Profile favorites section</td></tr>
<tr><td>Edit own clip</td><td>POST /api/clips/update-own</td><td>ClipEditModal</td></tr>
<tr><td>Delete own clip</td><td>Delete endpoints</td><td>Owner actions in modal</td></tr>
</table>

<h4>Clip Playback</h4>
<ul>
<li><strong>StreamVideoPlayer</strong> &mdash; Cloudflare Stream HLS playback</li>
<li><strong>ClipModal</strong> &mdash; full-screen viewer with swipe navigation between clips</li>
<li><strong>Deep links</strong> &mdash; ?clip=&lt;id&gt; URL param opens modal via ClipDeepLinkHandler</li>
<li><strong>Feed preview limiter</strong> &mdash; caps concurrent autoplay videos in feeds</li>
</ul>

<h4>Clip Metadata Model (post-migration 54)</h4>
<p>Key fields: artist_name, venue_name, location, song_title, song_slug, genre_name, genre_slug, event_title, show_id, jambase_event_id, jambase_artist_id, jambase_venue_id, geolocation, video_status, stream_playback_url, engagement counters, is_trending_score, average_rating</p>

<h3>4. Feed &amp; Discovery</h3>

<h4>Home Feed (/)</h4>
<table>
<tr><th>Mode</th><th>Behavior</th></tr>
<tr><td>Logged out</td><td>Hero section, latest/trending clips, nearby shows CTA</td></tr>
<tr><td>Logged in</td><td>MainFeedStack: favorite-artist panel, personalized feed, YouTube, shows</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Feed features: infinite scroll (IntersectionObserver), filters (Latest / Trending / Most Liked / Top Rated), skeleton loading, empty states, favorite-artist feed panel.</p>

