<h2>Developer Onboarding Checklist</h2>
<ol>
<li>npm install</li>
<li>Copy .dev.vars.example &rarr; .dev.vars and fill secrets</li>
<li>npm run db:migrate:local</li>
<li>npm run dev (or npm run dev:worker for full Cloudflare emulation)</li>
<li>Read docs/cloudflare-setup.md for production resource wiring</li>
<li>Run npm test to verify unit tests pass</li>
<li>Run npm run check before deploy</li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2>Summary Assessment</h2>
<p>MOMENTUM is a <strong>substantial, production-architected</strong> live-music social platform. The <strong>core loop</strong> &mdash; capture &rarr; upload &rarr; discover &rarr; engage with clips &mdash; is functional end-to-end with rich metadata (shows, songs, genres, events), strong third-party integrations (JamBase, Ticketmaster, YouTube, music recognition), and a complete backend for social, gamification, payments, and admin.</p>
<p>The main gaps are <strong>frontend wiring</strong> for advanced features (live viewer, premium, role dashboards, settings pages) and <strong>test coverage</strong> beyond unit tests. The codebase has evolved significantly since the December 2024 status report, with 2026 work focused on show/event organization, notifications, and social refinement.</p>

<p class="meta" style="margin-top: 24pt;"><em>End of report. Generated June 8, 2026.</em></p>

